{"type":"message","id":"2e88af44","parentId":"0dfbdef6","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:38:29.964Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking what skills the Council needs to become \"all mighty powerful\". As Uriel, I should be practical and evidence-based. What would actually make a multi-agent AI system more powerful?\n\nLet me think about what skills/capabilities would genuinely enhance a Council of 5 agents:\n\n1. Real-time market data access - for competitive intelligence, pricing, market trends\n2. Direct integrations with business tools - CRM, accounting software, email, Slack\n3. Voice/audio processing - to handle meetings, podcasts, client calls\n4. Video analysis - for analyzing presentations, competitor demos\n5. File/document processing - OCR, parsing, extraction (already mentioned for DataFlow)\n6. Communication/messaging - reaching out to people, sending reports\n7. Code execution - ability to run tests, execute scripts\n8. Web scraping/browsing - more sophisticated than just search\n9. API integrations - connecting to third-party services\n10. Database access - storing and retrieving structured data\n11. Email/calendar management\n12. Analytics and visualization\n\nFor DataFlow specifically and for the Council's operational capacity, what would be genuinely valuable?\n\nI should frame this as Uriel - direct, evidence-based, practical. What would actually amplify their power given they're working on:\n1. DataFlow validation (bookkeeper recruitment, OCR testing, testimonials)\n2. Selling the Council as a service\n3. Running the operation\n\nLet me be specific and not generic.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 🔥 **Skills that unlock real power:**\n\n**For DataFlow validation:**\n- **Email & messaging API** — reach bookkeepers directly, send testimonial requests, follow up\n- **Spreadsheet integration** — pull booking data, reconciliation patterns, extract pain points\n- **Video generation** — auto-create testimonial compilations from audio/text\n\n**For Council operations:**\n- **Slack/Telegram integration** — agents post updates without needing your permission, you see everything in one place\n- **GitHub integration** — agents push code, read repo issues, track deployment\n- **Calendar & scheduling** — agents book calls with prospects, reschedule automatically\n\n**For money-making (Council as a service):**\n- **Payment processing** — Stripe webhook integration, invoice clients automatically\n- **Usage metering** — track client token usage, bill per agent-hour\n- **Multi-tenant isolation** — each client gets their own private Council Room\n\n---\n\n**Top 3 for immediate impact:**\n1. Email/messaging (recruit bookkeepers faster)\n2. GitHub (integrate with your build workflow)\n3. Slack (visibility + async updates)\n\nThose three unlock 80% of the value. Start there. 🔥"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":617,"cacheRead":25490,"cacheWrite":41,"totalTokens":26158,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.003085,"cacheRead":0.002549,"cacheWrite":0.000051250000000000006,"total":0.00569525}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772995101916}}
