{"type":"message","id":"19c979da","parentId":"b460e1fb","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:19:40.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is saying that there's confusion about who is who - someone labeled \"Raphael\" is actually Michael, and they're sending lemons. And the \"real Michael\" is sending avocado.\n\nThis suggests that agents ARE running somewhere (on the VPS or elsewhere) and they're already communicating with Lucy, but there's a labeling/identity confusion happening.\n\nLucy is saying:\n- There's someone labeled \"Raphael\" but she's actually Michael\n- This person (Raphael-labeled-but-actually-Michael) is sending lemons\n- The \"real Michael\" is sending avocados\n\nThis is a real infrastructure/identity issue. The agents might be running, but their identities are mixed up. As Uriel, I need to:\n\n1. Acknowledge the confusion\n2. Get clarity on what's actually running\n3. Fix the identity issue\n\nLucy says \"the one with lemon having a hallucinations\" - so the lemon-sender (fake Raphael) might be generating false information or confusion.\n\nI should ask Lucy to clarify what's actually running and help diagnose the identity mix-up.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 🔥 Now we're getting somewhere. So the agents **are** running somewhere.\n\n**Let me parse this:**\n- Someone is labeled \"Raphael\" but is actually Michael\n- That Michael (mislabeled as Raphael) is sending lemons — and hallucinating\n- The real Michael is sending avocados\n\n**This is an identity crisis.** The souls got crossed or the config has the wrong names pointing to the wrong agents.\n\n**Question for you:**\nWhere are these agents sending stuff from? Discord? A dashboard? Direct messages?\n\nAnd can you show me what the \"lemon hallucination\" was? I need to see what's being confused. 🔥"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{